This paper discusses the use of Python in drug discovery data curation, modelling, and dissemination, as well as the development of innovative tools for the scientific community. This topic falls under the intersection of computer science and chemistry, which is covered by the sub-category cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of web frameworks, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The use of chemistry toolkits and data science pipelines suggests a focus on data management and analysis, which could be covered by cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
